From: Gilly <gilroyscott1970@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: connac: fix possible NULL deref in mt76_connac_mcu_uni_bss_he_tlv

Backport of Lorenzo Bianconi's linux-wireless series (1/4).
mt76_connac_get_he_phy_cap() can return NULL when the band carries no HE
capability; mt76_connac_mcu_uni_bss_he_tlv() dereferences the result via
cap->he_mcs_nss_supp without checking. Bail out early on NULL.

--- a/mt76_connac_mcu.c
+++ b/mt76_connac_mcu.c
@@ -1441,6 +1441,8 @@
 	struct bss_info_uni_he *he;
 
 	cap = mt76_connac_get_he_phy_cap(phy, vif);
+	if (!cap)
+		return;
 
 	he = (struct bss_info_uni_he *)tlv;
 	he->he_pe_duration = vif->bss_conf.htc_trig_based_pkt_ext;
